{"title_page": "Joint Institute for VLBI ERIC", "text_new": "[[File:JIVE full logo.png|alt=Full JIVE logo featuring a star and the text JIVE, Joint Institute for VLBI ERIC|thumb|263x263px|Full JIVE logo]]\n{{Infobox Organization\n|name         = Joint Institute for VLBI ERIC\n|image        = \n|image_border = \n|size         = 300px\n|caption      = Logo of the JIVE Organization\n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1993\n|extinction   = \n|type         = \n|status       = \n|purpose      = Operate the [[European VLBI Network|EVN]] and provide support to [[VLBI]] astronomers.\n|headquarters = \n|location     = 7990 AA Dwingeloo, The Netherlands\n|region_served =\n|membership   = \n|language     = \n|leader_title = \n|leader_name  = \n|main_organ   = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations = \n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers =\n|budget       = \n|website      = http://www.jive.eu\n|remarks      =\n}}\n\nThe '''Joint Institute for Very Long Baseline Interferometry European Research Infrastructure Consortium (JIVE)''' was established by a decision of the European Commission in December 2014, and assumed the activities and responsibilities of the JIVE foundation, which was established in December 1993. JIVE's mandate is to support the operations and users of the [[European VLBI Network|European VLBI Network (EVN)]], in the widest sense.   \n\nVery Long Baseline Interferometry ([[VLBI]]) is a type of [[astronomical interferometry]] used in [[radio astronomy]]. It allows observations of an object that are made simultaneously by many telescopes to be combined, emulating a telescope with a size equal to the maximum separation between the telescopes. Normally the participating radio telescopes function individually, working on their own specific projects. In the case of VLBI, they all observe the same source at the same time, allowing much higher spatial resolution. There are many complex and challenging hurdles that need to be overcome to enable this effort. One challenge is the data processing requirement. JIVE operates the EVN data processor, known as the correlator - a special-purpose [[supercomputer]] for [[astronomical]] [[VLBI]] data correlation. \n\n=== Organisation of JIVE ===\nJIVE is located in Dwingeloo, the Netherlands and is hosted by the Netherlands Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[ASTRON]]).\n\nJIVE has six members:\n\n* The Netherlands, represented by the [[Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research]] (NWO) and the Netherlands Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[ASTRON]])\n* France, represented by the National Center for Scientific Research ([[CNRS]])\n* Latvia, represented by the Ministry of Education and Science ([https://izm.gov.lv/en/ IZM])\n* Spain, represented by the Ministry of Development ([https://www.mitma.gob.es/ MF])\n* Sweden, represented by the Swedish Research Council ([https://www.vr.se/english.html VR])\n* The United Kingdom, represented by the [[Science and Technology Facilities Council]] (STFC)\n\nJIVE is also supported by the following participating research institutes:\n\n* National Astronomical Observatories of China ([[National Astronomical Observatory of China|NAOC]]), China\n* Max Planck Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[MPIfR]]), Germany\n\n* National Institute for Astrophysics ([[INAF]]), Italy\n*National Research Federation ([[National Research Foundation (South Africa)|NRF]]), South Africa\n\nThere are currently [https://www.evlbi.org/telescopes 22 telescopes] in the EVN. \n\nObservations using the EVN can also be carried out in real-time, thus earning the name of e-VLBI (electronic Very Long Baseline Interferometry). The telescopes are then linked via high-speed [[national research and education networks]] (NRENs) which overcome some of the performance drawbacks of [[TCP/IP]] and [[UDP/IP]] (networking protocols) to allow sharing large volumes of data for immediate use. Such high-speed networks eliminate the shipping of disks of data from separate observations for correlation, thus allowing astronomers to respond to events as they happen in real time. The [[VLBI]] data are streamed to JIVE, where they are correlated and the final, high-resolution image created.\n\nIn a demonstration of e-VLBI as part of 100 Hours of Astronomy<ref>{{cite press release | title = European VLBI Network to participate in \"100 Hours of Astronomy\" with live webcast and e-VLBI observations | publisher = JIVE | date = 2009-03-16 | url = http://www.jive.nl/press_release_EVN_100Hrs.html | accessdate = 2009-07-15 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090719182456/http://www.jive.nl/press_release_EVN_100Hrs.html | archivedate = 2009-07-19 }}</ref> in 2009 14 telescopes from Australia, Chile, China, Finland, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Poland, [[Puerto Rico]], Spain, Sweden and the UK participated in joint observations of the active galaxy 3C120. The participating telescopes included:<ref>{{cite web | last = Verkouter | first = Harro | title = April 3 and 5th 2009 | url = http://iya.expres-eu.org/index.html | accessdate = 2009-07-15 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20090712044638/http://iya.expres-eu.org/index.html | archivedate = 2009-07-12 }}</ref>\n\n* the 26 meter telescope at [[Hobart]], operated by the [[University of Tasmania]];\n* the 22m dish of Mopra, part of the Long Baseline Array, operated by [[CSIRO]];\n* the 25m dish of [[Sheshan Island|Sheshan]] near [[Shanghai]], operated by the [[Shanghai Astronomical Observatory]], [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]];\n* the 14m [[Mets\u00e4hovi Radio Observatory|Mets\u00e4hovi]] dish, operated by the [[Aalto University]];\n* the 32m telescope of [[Toru\u0144]];\n* the 32m telescope at [[Medicina]], operated by the [[Instituto Nazionale di Astrofisica]];\n* the 25m telescope at the [[Onsala Space Observatory]];\n* the [[Westerbork Synthesis Radio Telescope]];\n* the [[Yebes Observatory RT40m|Yebes 40m]], operated by the [[Spanish National Observatory|Observatorio Astronomico Nacional]];\n* the 300m dish of [[Arecibo]], located in [[Puerto Rico]];\n* the 6m dish of TIGO, operated by the Geod\u00e4tisches Observatorium Wettzell.\n\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n\n* JIVE [http://www.jive.eu/ Website]\n* Arecibo Observatory History [https://web.archive.org/web/20090314225635/http://www.history.com/encyclopedia.do?vendorId=FWNE.fw..ar136000.a Website]\n* Quasar 3C454.3 from The Institute of Physics [http://www.iop.org/EJ/article/1538-4357/464/1/L55/5087.text.html Website]\n\n{{Radio-astronomy|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Astronomy in Europe]]\n[[Category:Astronomy institutes and departments]]\n[[Category:Interferometry]]\n[[Category:International research institutes]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:JIVE full logo.png|alt=Full JIVE logo featuring a star and the text JIVE, Joint Institute for VLBI ERIC|thumb|263x263px|Full JIVE logo]]\n{{Infobox Organization\n|name         = Joint Institute for VLBI ERIC\n|image        = \n|image_border = \n|size         = 300px\n|caption      = Logo of the JIVE Organization\n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1993\n|extinction   = \n|type         = \n|status       = \n|purpose      = Operate the [[European VLBI Network|EVN]] and provide support to [[VLBI]] astronomers.\n|headquarters = \n|location     = 7990 AA Dwingeloo, The Netherlands\n|region_served =\n|membership   = \n|language     = \n|leader_title = \n|leader_name  = \n|main_organ   = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations = \n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers =\n|budget       = \n|website      = http://www.jive.eu\n|remarks      =\n}}\n\nThe '''Joint Institute for Very Long Baseline Interferometry European Research Infrastructure Consortium (JIVE)''' was established be a decision of the European Commission in December 2014, and assumed the activities and responsibilities of the JIVE foundation, which was established in December 1993. JIVE's mandate is to support the operations and users of the [[European VLBI Network|European VLBI Network (EVN)]], in the widest sense.   \n\nVery Long Baseline Interferometry ([[VLBI]]) is a type of [[astronomical interferometry]] used in [[radio astronomy]]. It allows observations of an object that are made simultaneously by many telescopes to be combined, emulating a telescope with a size equal to the maximum separation between the telescopes. Normally the participating radio telescopes function individually, working on their own specific projects. In the case of VLBI, they all observe the same source at the same time, allowing much higher spatial resolution. There are many complex and challenging hurdles that need to be overcome to enable this effort. One challenge is the data processing requirement. JIVE operates the EVN data processor, known as the correlator - a special-purpose [[supercomputer]] for [[astronomical]] [[VLBI]] data correlation. \n\n=== Organisation of JIVE ===\nJIVE is located in Dwingeloo, the Netherlands and is hosted by the Netherlands Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[ASTRON]]).\n\nJIVE has six members:\n\n* The Netherlands, represented by the [[Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research]] (NWO) and the Netherlands Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[ASTRON]])\n* France, represented by the National Center for Scientific Research ([[CNRS]])\n* Latvia, represented by the Ministry of Education and Science ([https://izm.gov.lv/en/ IZM])\n* Spain, represented by the Ministry of Development ([https://www.mitma.gob.es/ MF])\n* Sweden, represented by the Swedish Research Council ([https://www.vr.se/english.html VR])\n* The United Kingdom, represented by the [[Science and Technology Facilities Council]] (STFC)\n\nJIVE is also supported by the following participating research institutes:\n\n* National Astronomical Observatories of China ([[National Astronomical Observatory of China|NAOC]]), China\n* Max Planck Institute for Radio Astronomy ([[MPIfR]]), Germany\n\n* National Institute for Astrophysics ([[INAF]]), Italy\n*National Research Federation ([[National Research Foundation (South Africa)|NRF]]), South Africa\n\nThere are currently [https://www.evlbi.org/telescopes 22 telescopes] in the EVN. \n\nObservations using the EVN can also be carried out in real-time, thus earning the name of e-VLBI (electronic Very Long Baseline Interferometry). The telescopes are then linked via high-speed [[national research and education networks]] (NRENs) which overcome some of the performance drawbacks of [[TCP/IP]] and [[UDP/IP]] (networking protocols) to allow sharing large volumes of data for immediate use. Such high-speed networks eliminate the shipping of disks of data from separate observations for correlation, thus allowing astronomers to respond to events as they happen in real time. The [[VLBI]] data are streamed to JIVE, where they are correlated and the final, high-resolution image created.\n\nIn a demonstration of e-VLBI as part of 100 Hours of Astronomy<ref>{{cite press release | title = European VLBI Network to participate in \"100 Hours of Astronomy\" with live webcast and e-VLBI observations | publisher = JIVE | date = 2009-03-16 | url = http://www.jive.nl/press_release_EVN_100Hrs.html | accessdate = 2009-07-15 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090719182456/http://www.jive.nl/press_release_EVN_100Hrs.html | archivedate = 2009-07-19 }}</ref> in 2009 14 telescopes from Australia, Chile, China, Finland, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Poland, [[Puerto Rico]], Spain, Sweden and the UK participated in joint observations of the active galaxy 3C120. The participating telescopes included:<ref>{{cite web | last = Verkouter | first = Harro | title = April 3 and 5th 2009 | url = http://iya.expres-eu.org/index.html | accessdate = 2009-07-15 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20090712044638/http://iya.expres-eu.org/index.html | archivedate = 2009-07-12 }}</ref>\n\n* the 26 meter telescope at [[Hobart]], operated by the [[University of Tasmania]];\n* the 22m dish of Mopra, part of the Long Baseline Array, operated by [[CSIRO]];\n* the 25m dish of [[Sheshan Island|Sheshan]] near [[Shanghai]], operated by the [[Shanghai Astronomical Observatory]], [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]];\n* the 14m [[Mets\u00e4hovi Radio Observatory|Mets\u00e4hovi]] dish, operated by the [[Aalto University]];\n* the 32m telescope of [[Toru\u0144]];\n* the 32m telescope at [[Medicina]], operated by the [[Instituto Nazionale di Astrofisica]];\n* the 25m telescope at the [[Onsala Space Observatory]];\n* the [[Westerbork Synthesis Radio Telescope]];\n* the [[Yebes Observatory RT40m|Yebes 40m]], operated by the [[Spanish National Observatory|Observatorio Astronomico Nacional]];\n* the 300m dish of [[Arecibo]], located in [[Puerto Rico]];\n* the 6m dish of TIGO, operated by the Geod\u00e4tisches Observatorium Wettzell.\n\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n\n* JIVE [http://www.jive.eu/ Website]\n* Arecibo Observatory History [https://web.archive.org/web/20090314225635/http://www.history.com/encyclopedia.do?vendorId=FWNE.fw..ar136000.a Website]\n* Quasar 3C454.3 from The Institute of Physics [http://www.iop.org/EJ/article/1538-4357/464/1/L55/5087.text.html Website]\n\n{{Radio-astronomy|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Astronomy in Europe]]\n[[Category:Astronomy institutes and departments]]\n[[Category:Interferometry]]\n[[Category:International research institutes]]\n", "name_user": "Ginamaffey", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint_Institute_for_VLBI_ERIC"}
{"title_page": "Les failles", "text_new": "{{Short description|Studio album by French singer Pomme}}\n{{Use American English|date = November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Les failles\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| cover        = Pomme - Les Failles Front artwork.png\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2019|11|01|df=yes}}\n| recorded     = <!-- Please source recording dates/years -->\n| studio       = \n| genre        = {{hlist|[[Folk rock]]|[[indie pop]]|[[chanson fran\u00e7aise]]}}\n| length       = {{Duration|m=35|s=29}}\n| label        = [[Polydor Records]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|Pomme|[[Albin de la Simone]]}}\n| prev_title   = [[\u00c0 peu pr\u00e8s]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| chronology   = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Les failles\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Je sais pas danser\n | single1date = August 30, 2019\n | single2     = Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\n | single2date = September 27, 2019\n}}\n}}\n'''''Les failles''''' ({{translation|\"The Faults\"}}) is the second studio album by French singer [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]], released on November 1, 2019 through [[Polydor Records]]. The album was produced by Pomme and [[Albin de la Simone]] and the lyrics were all written by Pomme.\n\n== Promotion ==\n\nPomme presented ''Les failles'' in the radio broadcasting program Popopop! of [[France Inter]], on October 29, 2019, where she performed the song \"Je sais pas danser\". In the program, Pomme announced a tour throughout France starting in January, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.franceinter.fr/emissions/popopop/popopop-29-octobre-2019|title=Samuel Blumenfeld et Pomme|last=de Caunes|first=Antoine|date=October 29, 2019|website=[[France Inter]]|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105062012/https://www.franceinter.fr/emissions/popopop/popopop-29-octobre-2019|archive-date=November 5, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\nIn August 30, \"Je sais pas danser\" was released as the first single of ''Les failles''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/je-sais-pas-danser-pomme/j8ta811ad4zyb|title=Je sais pas danser - Pomme|last=|first=|date=August 30, 2019|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122225443/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/je-sais-pas-danser-pomme/j8ta811ad4zyb|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> A month later, \"Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\" was released as the second single of the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/anxiete-pomme/f2aqq18qoscnc|title=Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9 - Pomme|last=|first=|date=September 27, 2019|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122225528/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/anxiete-pomme/f2aqq18qoscnc|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n{{Album reviews\n| rev1 = ''[[Le Devoir]]''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"ledevoir\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ledevoir.com/culture/musique/566556/chanson-les-failles|title=Les failles, Pomme|last=Cormier|first=Sylvain|date=November 8, 2019|website=[[Le Devoir]]|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108144958/https://www.ledevoir.com/culture/musique/566556/chanson-les-failles|archive-date=November 8, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n}}\n''Les failles'' received critical acclaim. ''[[Le Devoir]]''<nowiki/>'s Sylvain Cormier said \"this second album of the most [...] is of a sober elegance, of an exquisite taste in restraint\".<ref name=\"ledevoir\"/> Addict Culture's Camille Locatelli said that the album is \"sort of sensitive diary that she reveals with modesty and poetry\", adding that \"it's an intriguing mix of [[chanson fran\u00e7aise]] and dream folk\", and concluded that \"''Les failles'' is a jewel burning with truth, to listen by the fireside or in the dark. Perfect for rocking your fall, so\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://addict-culture.com/dans-la-tete-de-pomme/|title=Dans la t\u00eate de Pomme|last=Locatelli|first=Camille|date=2019-11-19|website=Addict Culture|language=fr-FR|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122223632/https://addict-culture.com/dans-la-tete-de-pomme/|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\n| writer1 = \n| length1 = 3:51\n| title2 = Je sais pas danser\n| writer2 = \n| length2 = 2:18\n| title3 = Grandiose\n| writer3 = \n| length3 = 3:16\n| title4 = Les s\u00e9quoias\n| writer4 = \n| length4 = 3:14\n| title5 = Les oiseaux\n| writer5 = \n| length5 = 3:16\n| title6 = Pourquoi la mort te fait peur?\n| writer6 = \n| length6 = 3:36\n| title7 = La lumi\u00e8re\n| writer7 = \n| length7 = 3:43\n| title8 = Soleil, soleil\n| writer8 = \n| length8 = 2:37\n| title9 = Saphir\n| writer9 = \n| length9 = 2:40\n| title10 = Une minute\n| writer10 = \n| length10 = 4:08\n| title11 = Chapelle\n| writer11 = \n| length11 = 2:50\n| all_writing = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| total_length = {{Duration|m=35|s=29}}\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from ''Les failles'' liner notes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Pomme-Les-Failles-/release/14369740|title=Pomme - Les Failles|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Discogs]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122204454/https://www.discogs.com/Pomme-Les-Failles-/release/14369740|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/les-failles-pomme/bdeode0ts4v2a|title=Album Les Failles, Pomme|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122204642/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/les-failles-pomme/bdeode0ts4v2a|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n'''Musicians'''\n\n* [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]] \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]], [[Arrangement|arrangements]], [[piano]] (track 1, 3), acoustic guitar (track 2, 4, 6, 8, 10), [[synthesizer]] (track 9)\n*Fran\u00e7ois Poggio \u2013 [[guitar]] (track 1), [[electric guitar]] (all tracks except 5, 9, 11)\n*[[Albin de la Simone]] \u2013 arrangements, drum programming (track 1), synthesizer programming (track 1, 3, ), synthesizer (track 4, 7, 8), [[bass guitar]] (track 2, 6), piano (track 2, 6, 7, 10), organ (track 6, 7)\n*Raphael Chassin \u2013 drums (track 1, 4), percussion (track 2, 3, 6, 7, 8, 10) \n*Ren\u00e9e Largeron \u2013 vocals (track 10)\n\n'''Design'''\n\n*Ambivalently Yours \u2013 [[illustration]], [[Design|graphic design]]\n\n'''Production'''\n\n* Albin de la Simone \u2013 [[Record producer|production]]\n* Pomme \u2013 production\n* Ghyslain-Luc Lavigne \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]], [[Audio engineer|engineering]]\n\n* \n\n'''Recording'''\n\n* Recorded at a personal studio\n\n*\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Austria ([[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/album/Pomme/Les-failles-393984|title=Pomme - Les failles|last=|first=|date=|website=hitparade.ch|publisher=Hung Medien|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122024357/https://hitparade.ch/album/Pomme/Les-failles-393984|archive-date=November 21, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n|87\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 200]] Wallonia)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Pomme|title=Discographie Pomme|last=|first=|date=|website=ultratop.be|publisher=Hung Medien|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122023435/https://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Pomme|archive-date=November 21, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n|68\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 albums]]\n[[Category:Pomme (singer) albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Studio album by French singer Pomme}}\n{{Use American English|date = November 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Les failles\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| cover        = Pomme - Les Failles Front artwork.png\n| alt          = \n| released     = {{Start date|2019|11|01|df=yes}}\n| recorded     = <!-- Please source recording dates/years -->\n| studio       = \n| genre        = {{hlist|[[Folk rock]]|[[indie pop]]|[[chanson fran\u00e7aise]]}}\n| length       = {{Duration|m=35|s=29}}\n| label        = [[Polydor Records]]\n| producer     = {{hlist|Pomme|[[Albin de la Simone]]}}\n| prev_title   = [[\u00c0 peu pr\u00e8s]]\n| prev_year    = 2018\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| chronology   = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Les failles\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Je sais pas danser\n | single1date = August 30, 2019\n | single2     = Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\n | single2date = September 27, 2019\n}}\n}}\n'''''Les failles''''' ({{translation|\"The Faults\"}}) is the second studio album by French singer [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]], released on November 1, 2019 through [[Polydor Records]]. The album was produced by Pomme and [[Albin de la Simone]] and the lyrics were all written by Pomme.\n\n== Promotion ==\n\nPomme presented ''Les failles'' in the radio broadcasting program Popopop! of [[France Inter]], on October 29, 2019, where she performed the song \"Je sais pas danser\". In the program, Pomme announced a tour throughout France starting in January, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.franceinter.fr/emissions/popopop/popopop-29-octobre-2019|title=Samuel Blumenfeld et Pomme|last=de Caunes|first=Antoine|date=October 29, 2019|website=[[France Inter]]|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105062012/https://www.franceinter.fr/emissions/popopop/popopop-29-octobre-2019|archive-date=November 5, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\nIn August 30, \"Je sais pas danser\" was released as the first single of ''Les failles''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/je-sais-pas-danser-pomme/j8ta811ad4zyb|title=Je sais pas danser - Pomme|last=|first=|date=August 30, 2019|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122225443/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/je-sais-pas-danser-pomme/j8ta811ad4zyb|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> A month later, \"Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\" was released as the second single of the album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/anxiete-pomme/f2aqq18qoscnc|title=Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9 - Pomme|last=|first=|date=September 27, 2019|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122225528/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/anxiete-pomme/f2aqq18qoscnc|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n{{Album reviews\n| rev1 = ''[[Le Devoir]]''\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"ledevoir\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ledevoir.com/culture/musique/566556/chanson-les-failles|title=Les failles, Pomme|last=Cormier|first=Sylvain|date=November 8, 2019|website=[[Le Devoir]]|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108144958/https://www.ledevoir.com/culture/musique/566556/chanson-les-failles|archive-date=November 8, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n}}\n''Les failles'' received critical acclaim. ''[[Le Devoir]]''<nowiki/>'s Sylvain Cormier said \"this second album of the most [...] is of a sober elegance, of an exquisite taste in restraint\".<ref name=\"ledevoir\"/> Addict Culture's Camille Locatelli said that the album is \"sort of sensitive diary that she reveals with modesty and poetry\", adding that \"it's an intriguing mix of [[chanson fran\u00e7aise]] and dream folk\", and concluded that \"''Les failles'' is a jewel burning with truth, to listen by the fireside or in the dark. Perfect for rocking your fall, so\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://addict-culture.com/dans-la-tete-de-pomme/|title=Dans la t\u00eate de Pomme|last=Locatelli|first=Camille|date=2019-11-19|website=Addict Culture|language=fr-FR|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122223632/https://addict-culture.com/dans-la-tete-de-pomme/|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = Anxi\u00e9t\u00e9\n| writer1 = \n| length1 = 3:51\n| title2 = Je sais pas danser\n| writer2 = \n| length2 = 2:18\n| title3 = Grandiose\n| writer3 = \n| length3 = 3:16\n| title4 = Les s\u00e9quoias\n| writer4 = \n| length4 = 3:14\n| title5 = Les oiseaux\n| writer5 = \n| length5 = 3:16\n| title6 = Pourquoi la mort te fait peur?\n| writer6 = \n| length6 = 3:36\n| title7 = La lumi\u00e8re\n| writer7 = \n| length7 = 3:43\n| title8 = Soleil, soleil\n| writer8 = \n| length8 = 2:37\n| title9 = Saphir\n| writer9 = \n| length9 = 2:40\n| title10 = Une minute\n| writer10 = \n| length10 = 4:08\n| title11 = Chapelle\n| writer11 = \n| length11 = 2:50\n| all_writing = [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]]\n| total_length = {{Duration|m=35|s=29}}\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from ''\u00c0 peu pr\u00e8s'' liner notes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Pomme-Les-Failles-/release/14369740|title=Pomme - Les Failles|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Discogs]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122204454/https://www.discogs.com/Pomme-Les-Failles-/release/14369740|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/les-failles-pomme/bdeode0ts4v2a|title=Album Les Failles, Pomme|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Qobuz]]|language=en-GB|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122204642/https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/les-failles-pomme/bdeode0ts4v2a|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n\n'''Musicians'''\n\n* [[Pomme (singer)|Pomme]] \u2013 [[Lead vocalist|lead vocals]], [[Arrangement|arrangements]], [[piano]] (track 1, 3), acoustic guitar (track 2, 4, 6, 8, 10), [[synthesizer]] (track 9)\n*Fran\u00e7ois Poggio \u2013 [[guitar]] (track 1), [[electric guitar]] (all tracks except 5, 9, 11)\n*[[Albin de la Simone]] \u2013 arrangements, drum programming (track 1), synthesizer programming (track 1, 3, ), synthesizer (track 4, 7, 8), [[bass guitar]] (track 2, 6), piano (track 2, 6, 7, 10), organ (track 6, 7)\n*Raphael Chassin \u2013 drums (track 1, 4), percussion (track 2, 3, 6, 7, 8, 10) \n*Ren\u00e9e Largeron \u2013 vocals (track 10)\n\n'''Design'''\n\n*Ambivalently Yours \u2013 [[illustration]], [[Design|graphic design]]\n\n'''Production'''\n\n* Albin de la Simone \u2013 [[Record producer|production]]\n* Pomme \u2013 production\n* Ghyslain-Luc Lavigne \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]], [[Audio engineer|engineering]]\n\n* \n\n'''Recording'''\n\n* Recorded at a personal studio\n\n* \n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Austria ([[\u00d63 Austria Top 40]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/album/Pomme/Les-failles-393984|title=Pomme - Les failles|last=|first=|date=|website=hitparade.ch|publisher=Hung Medien|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122024357/https://hitparade.ch/album/Pomme/Les-failles-393984|archive-date=November 21, 2019|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref>\n|87\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Belgium ([[Ultratop|Ultratop 200]] Wallonia)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Pomme|